Create a page for every university and college and add {{infobox University}} for it. See the missing list for those institutions still awaiting articles. Place {{WikiProject Higher education}} on every related talk page. Combat boosterism wherever it appears Ensure all articles, including Featured articles, are consistent with the article guidelines. This page is about improving articles about higher education. For using Wikipedia in education, see Wikipedia:Student assignments. WikiProject Higher education aims to improve the coverage of universities and colleges on Wikipedia. Please feel free to join our project by adding your name at the List of participants and including this page on your watchlist. Standardize the structure and content of all college and university articles Ensure colleges' and universities' articles comply with Wikipedia's five pillars Improve the coverage of higher education, propelling articles to featured status Serve as the central hub for all discussions and information related to higher education coverage Add missing and requested higher education articles Task forces are meant to provide centralized information and a discussion area for topics that have a sufficiently large scope, but that would not benefit from having a separate WikiProject with all of the additional work that would involve. This WikiProject formerly had the Student Affairs task force, but it is now inactive. Geographic areas, athletic conferences, or individual institutions with multiple pages and the interest of several active Wikipedians may become the subject of a sub-project. Propose the new project on the WikiProject Higher education talk page or at the WikiProject Council to make sure there is enough interest before starting a new project. See the related projects section for examples. You can link to a college's page by finding its IPEDS ID at nces.ed.gov/collegenavigator (not the OPE ID) and using the following template. {{College-navigator|}} For example, Valparaiso University's ID is 152600. Therefore, this template produces Valparaiso University at College Navigator, a tool from the National Center for Education Statistics You can use an optional second parameter to specify a name other than the title of the Wikipedia page that calls the template. {{College-navigator|152600|Valparaiso University (Indiana)}} produces: Valparaiso University (Indiana) at College Navigator, a tool from the National Center for Education Statistics Click on "►" below to display subcategories: Click on "►" below to display subcategories: List of all subpages of this page Ranking of colleges by number of alumni with Wikipedia pages WikiProject Bangladeshi Universities WikiProject Education in Canada WikiProject Education in India Note: Most of these projects are inactive, and creating new projects for individual institutions is not recommended.
